"Let me give some historical perspective as to why it has the reputation of being harder to learn than it is. Back in the Stone Age, when I learned bridge, standard American (it was not called SAYC then) was much simpler. Basically, we played Stayman, transfers, and Blackwood, pretty much that was it.  That was the system played by most beginners and intermediates."|
