^-|CP||FP||at|^C@2^y@3For me, One Notrump Forcing response to one of a major opening was a bit confusing and difficult to learn.  However, I divided the puzzle into several manageable sections so I can learn it with less difficulty. Let me start by looking at five possible hand types after partner opens one of a major and we are playing 2 over 1. Further, please note that I use the generic term of "points" here. I use Bergen's method to evaluate my hand. You may choose a different method. Therefore you may have to adjust the numbers given blow.|
