^-|HT|F|AT|^B@2^Y@3To better understand opener's rebid options based on various hands here is several quizzes. The correct answer (remember not all experts agree) and a short explanation follow. This section again is adopted from my various sources including the "The Two over One System" by Mike Lawrence and programmed by Fred Gitelman. For ease of use I have modified the format and summarized the explanation in a few of the examples. As always, the study of pertinent sources i.e. CDs, books and web sites is a must. In all the boards you are sitting South. Your partner has bid a game force. Please choose the appropriate bid for each hand.|
