st||sk||rh||ah|OPENER'S REBID OPTIONS|ah|Quiz|ah|Board  3|sv|0|md|1sakjhaj873dj8ckjt,,|mb|1hp2dp?|lb|*BWhat bid would you make?^^2n|mb|2n|NT|
^b@2^*B2NT^*N is the right bid.  The expectation is that partner will bid 3NT.  When he does that, you will follow with 4NT saying that you really have a good hand of about eighteen or nineteen points.  This is just one of many Two Over One bidding tricks that you will like to have available.  This sequence is much better than the solution chosen by some which is to ask for Aces and then bid 6NT.  6NT may be a good contract or a bad one.  Better to show your hand and get your partner's opinion. Again, some experts may bid 3NT here and follow up after responder's rebid.|
pg| ***** 226 ***** |


NT||

