%%%%%%%%%%%%%b 8
st||sk||rh||ah|OPENER'S REBID OPTIONS|ah|Quiz|ah|Board 8|sv|0|md|1s73hk7643dakjcak8,,|mb|1hp2dp?|lb|*BWhat bid would you make?^^3d|mb|3d|NT|
^b@2^*B3D^*N is right.  Even though you have a huge hand, the raise is best.  You will get another chance because your partner has committed the hand to a game contract.  (Even though I always refer to a two over one bid being game forcing, there is always the slim chance that you might stop in four of a minor if you can't find a major suit fit and if 3NT is not playable.)|
pg| ***** 236 ***** |


NT|| 

%%%%%%%%%%%%%b9
st||sk||rh||ah|OPENER'S REBID OPTIONS|ah|Quiz|ah|Board 9|sv|0|md|1sa93hkqj84d3caq85,,|mb|1hp2dp?|lb|*BWhat bid would you make?^^3c|mb|3c|NT|
^b@2This depends on your partnership agreements. If you play you can bid a new suit at the three level, you should bid ^*B3C^*N. Going to the three level does show extra values and you have them.  Better yet, as I learned to play reverse in 2 over 1 then 3C is my bid which is a reverse and shows five Hearts and four clubs. |
pg| ***** 238 ***** |


