%%%%%%%%%%%%%b11
st||sk||rh||ah|OPENER'S REBID OPTIONS|ah|Quiz|ah|Board 11|sv|0|md|1sqj873hk82daq6c83,,|mb|1sp2hp?|lb|*BWhat bid would you make?^^3h|mb|3h|NT|
^b@2Bid ^*B3H^*N.  Do not bid four.  Some players use a jump to game to show a minimum hand.  The problem with that is that your partner has no room to discover if your hand fits well for slam without getting to the five level.  A jump to game must show specific information that your partner can use.|
pg| ***** 243 ***** |


NT||

%%%%%%%%%%%%%b12
st||sk||rh||ah|OPENER'S REBID OPTIONS|ah|Quiz|ah|Board 12|sv|0|md|1skq874hkqt4dq8ct4,,|mb|1sp2hp?|lb|*BWhat bid would you make?^^4h|mb|4h|NT|
^b@2You can bid ^*B4H^*N with this hand.  The jump says you have good spades, good hearts, no Ace or king or singleton in the unbid suits, and not much extra either.  This is an important understanding to have.  If you routinely jump to game with many of your hands that have trump support, your partner will wonder which one you have.|
pg| ***** 245 ***** |


NT||

%%%%%%%%%%%%%b13
st||sk||rh||ah|OPENER'S REBID OPTIONS|ah|Quiz|ah|Board 13|sv|0|md|1saqjt4hkq84dq8cj3,,|mb|1sp2hp?|lb|*BWhat bid would you make?^^3h|mb|3h|NT|
^b@2This hand is too good to bid 4H.  Just bid 3H.  You could have a slam if your partner's hand fits well.  Some judgment is needed here.|
pg| ***** 247 ***** |


NT||

%%%%%%%%%%%%%b14
st||sk||rh||ah|OPENER'S REBID OPTIONS|ah|Quiz|ah|Board 14|sv|0|md|1skq764haqtdak3c73,,|mb|1sp2hp?|lb|*BWhat bid would you make?^^3h|mb|3h|NT|
^b@2Bid ^*B3H^*N.  This is a very good hand and you do not intend to stop in 4H.  You intend to force this hand to the five level at least and will be disappointed if there is no slam.  For the moment, bidding 3H, forcing to game, is the way to start your hunt for slam.|
pg| ***** 249 ***** |


NT||

%%%%%%%%%%%%%b15
st||sk||rh||ah|OPENER'S REBID OPTIONS|ah|Quiz|ah|Board 15|sv|0|md|1saj874hkj32dkj8c2,,|mb|1sp2hp?|lb|*BWhat bid would you make?^^4c|mb|4c|NT|
^b@2Splinter to ^*B4C^*N.  You don't have much more than a minimum but what you have is nice.  Your four card support is nice too.  You might do this with just three, but it won't be that common.  NOTE that your partner's 2H bid promises five of them.  This is the only Two Over One bid that guarantees a five card suit.  This is one of those 99% promises that your partner may choose to violate but if he has done so, it is with reason.|
pg| ***** 251 ***** |


NT||

%%%%%%%%%%%%%b16
st||sk||rh||ah|OPENER'S REBID OPTIONS|ah|Quiz|ah|Board 16|sv|0|md|1saj763ht6dajckt74,,|mb|1sp2hp?|lb|*BWhat bid would you make?^^2n|mb|2n|NT|
^b@2Bid ^*B2NT^*N.  There is a fact of bidding that some players never learn.  I will put it to you in a rule, "IF YOU HAVE A HAND THAT LOOKS LIKE IT QUALIFIES FOR A NOTRUMP BID AND IF THERE IS NO GOOD REASON NOT TO DO SO, MAKE THAT BID. A 2NT bid here makes life easy on your partner.  It implies a balanced hand.  It shows your range of points.  It suggests stoppers in the unbid suits.  All information your partner can use. Because your notrump bid promises two or more cards in your partner's suit, he knows that you have a tolerance for it and that there is no real misfit.  A notrump bid by you really does help your partner's bidding decision.  That is a promise" --Mike Lawrence. |
pg| ***** 253 ***** |


NT||

%%%%%%%%%%%%%b17
st||sk||rh||ah|OPENER'S REBID OPTIONS|ah|Quiz|ah|Board 17|sv|0|md|1sj8652hakdaj3c873,,|mb|1sp2hp?|lb|*BWhat bid would you make?^^2s|mb|2s|NT|
^b@2Bid ^*B2S^*N.  This won't feel good to a lot of players who like to promise a six card suit.  But it feels good to me.  The idea is that there is no BETTER bid to make.  I will not raise hearts without three.  And I will not bid notrump with three little clubs.  Since my partner must have three spades to raise me, even though the suit was rebid, I do not worry that I will play in a 5-2 fit.  I would, in fact, rebid 2S with this hand if my spades were even worse.  Rebidding your suit, is the least special of your rebids.|
pg| ***** 255 ***** |


NT||

%%%%%%%%%%%%%b18
st||sk||rh||ah|OPENER'S REBID OPTIONS|ah|Quiz|ah|Board 18|sv|0|md|1sakj74hakda53c763,,|mb|1sp2hp?|lb|*BWhat bid would you make?^^2s|mb|2s|NT|
^b@2Bid ^*B2S^*N again.  Rebidding your suit is a neutral expression.  You may have a minimum as on the previous hand or a big hand such as you have here.|
pg| ***** 257 ***** |


NT||

%%%%%%%%%%%%%b19
st||sk||rh||ah|OPENER'S REBID OPTIONS|ah|Quiz|ah|Board 19|sv|0|md|1sq8763hq8dakjcj73,,|mb|1sp2hp?|lb|*BWhat bid would you make?^^2n|mb|2n|NT|
^b@2Bid ^*B2NT^*N.  You hate to bid 2NT with a completely unstopped suit because you may be in danger even if partner has something in the suit.  When you have three to the jack, as you have in clubs, you do not have to be paranoid about your chances in notrump.  If your partner has a club card, it will combine with your holding to give you a sure stopper.  If your hand really looks like notrump and if you have a partial stopper, you can reasonably bid 2NT.|
pg| ***** 259 ***** |


