^B@2This is an odd one.  It is generally agreed that a 2NT rebid shows twelve to fourteen points OR eighteen to nineteen.  When you have twelve to fourteen, the bidding continues normally.  When you have the eighteen or nineteen point hand, you bid 2NT and then surprise your partner with some unexpected bidding.  He will get the message and will reassess where the hand should be played.

^B@2This brings up the 3NT bid.  It is logical to play 3NT shows fifteen to seventeen with a five card major, but if you like to open 1NT with this range of hands, then you won't have much call for the 3NT rebid.

After discussing this with a variety of players, most of whom shrugged their shoulders and claimed ignorance, I have come to the following conclusion.|
